 THE President, Nigeria Union of Traders Association Ghana, NUTAG, Mr Chukwuemeka Nnaji, has confirmed the reopening of hundreds of Nigerians’ shops shut in Ghana after three months. November 9, 2018 In "News" FOR once in a long while some diplomatic efforts to alleviate the sufferings of Nigerians living in foreign lands appear to be recording a heart-warming breakthrough. Shops and small businesses belonging to Nigerians – about 400 in all – shut by the Ghanaian authorities are gradually being reopened. November 14, 2018 In "Editorial" Nigeria has expressed concern over the continued closure of Nigerians shops in Ghana two weeks after President Koffi Nana-Akudo gave the order to reopen them. October 11, 2018 In "Business"